Bring a #medium pot{} of @salt{and water} to a boil. Wash and dry all produce.

Core, deseed, and dice @bell pepper{1}(cored, deseeded, and diced) into ½-inch pieces. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}(trimmed and thinly sliced), separating whites from greens.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{2%tsp} in a large, preferably nonstick, #pan{} over medium-high heat. Add bell pepper and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook until lightly browned and slightly softened, ~{3-4%minutes}. Add scallion whites and cook until softened, ~{1-2%minutes}. Remove veggies from pan.

Return pan over medium-high heat with another large drizzle of olive oil; add @ground plant-based protein{9%oz}. Using a #spatula{}, press into an even layer. Cook, without stirring, until browned on bottom, ~{3-4%minutes}. Break up protein into pieces and continue cooking until browned all over and warmed through, ~{3-4%minutes} more. Return veggies to pan and stir to combine.

Once water is boiling, add @rigatoni pasta{6%oz} to #pot{}. Cook until al dente, ~{10-12%minutes}.

Reserve ½ cup pasta cooking water, then drain.

While pasta cooks, stir @Italian seasoning{1%tbsp}, @tomato paste{1.5%oz}, and @sugar{1%tsp} (2 tsp for 4 servings) into pan with veggie mixture until combined.

Stir in @cream cheese{4%tbsp} and ¾ cup plain water (1¼ cups for 4). Bring to a simmer and cook, stirring, until sauce is combined and thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Reduce heat to low and stir in half the @Parmesan cheese{¼%oz} (save the rest for serving). Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Add drained rigatoni and @butter{1%tbsp} (2 TBSP for 4 servings) to pan with sauce; stir to coat. If needed, stir in reserved pasta cooking water a splash at a time until pasta is coated in a creamy sauce. Taste and season with salt and pepper.

Divide pasta between #bowls{}. Top with scallion greens and remaining Parmesan. Serve.

> This dish tastes like meat without the meat, perfect for plant-based eaters craving a comforting pasta.